reviews.review_text: Great Sound This is crunch, really crystal clear.  '85 the way it should sound.

Could have been a spoonful of coffee.. SBD???...Sounds like a Matrix to my ears..call me crazy..some says I am..some says I aint!! ANYWAY I likey..One of my favorite 1st sets from 85' in there with 4/8,!!6/27!!,10/29,11/21..so please..GIVE IT A WHIRL!!!! Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!!LIFER>>>>

most fun I saw every show in 85 from hampton in march to meadowlands in november. This show is easily my favorite of the year. It was incredibly fun,The dancing for china rider was like the entire crowd turned into olympic athletes or something. The monster bounce. Also it is important to note that matt kelly plays the harp on the smokestack that came outta nowhere.

Best show I ever saw And it was my friend's first Dead show! I was enveloped in a deep, dark purple haze, and so my memories of the night are dim -- I was surprised to see the set list! -- but all I remember is that the band were on psychedelic fire all night. I highly recommend this show. Can't wait to hear it again.
